Package com.example.mapruler

Class Route

java.lang.Object
com.example.mapruler.Route
public class Route extends Object
Data object used to store all of the information for a route. Contains all of the destinations and stops. Able to be directly stored in firebase.

  • Constructor Details

    • Route

      public Route(String name, ArrayList<com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng> coordinates, ArrayList<String> addresses, boolean fromCurrentLocation)
      Public constructor for the Route object, creates new, fully filled out
      Parameters:
      name - visible name for the route, will show in the list view
      coordinates - ArrayList of LatLng points that the route will go through
      addresses - ArrayList of the addresses/names associated with the coordinates
      fromCurrentLocation - whether the current route starts at a given location or current location.

  • Method Details

    • addCurrentLocation

      public Route addCurrentLocation(com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng currLatLon)
      Method used to create a new route object by prepending the given current location to the beginning of a route that starts at current location. Will do nothing if the route is already starting from a given location.
      Parameters:
      currLatLon - LatLng object of the current location of the user
      Returns:
      new Route object with currLatLon prepended.
